HEADWORD: Eyesight
<hw>Eye"sight`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Sight of the eye;
the sense of seeing; view; observation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Josephus sets this down from his own <qex>eyesight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Wilkins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eyesore</ent>⟦br⟧
